#    FAIRification 0.3.1: term definitions (rdfs:comment) for previously label-only terms
#################################################################

kcro:ClusterRole rdfs:comment "A cluster-scoped RBAC role: a named set of permission rules that applies across all namespaces. Modelled as a permission resource kind."@en .
kcro:ConfigMap rdfs:comment "A Kubernetes object holding non-confidential configuration data as key-value pairs, consumed by pods as environment variables or mounted files. Modelled as a data resource kind."@en .
kcro:CronJob rdfs:comment "A workload kind that creates Jobs on a repeating schedule. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:DaemonSet rdfs:comment "A workload kind that ensures a copy of a pod runs on every (or selected) node. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:DataResource rdfs:comment "Abstract grouping of Kubernetes kinds whose purpose is to hold data consumed by workloads, such as ConfigMap and Secret."@en .
kcro:Deployment rdfs:comment "A workload kind that manages a replicated, declaratively updated set of pods via a pod template. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:Ingress rdfs:comment "A Kubernetes object that manages external HTTP/HTTPS access to Services, including routing rules and optional TLS termination. Modelled as a network resource kind."@en .
kcro:Job rdfs:comment "A workload kind that runs one or more pods to completion. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:NetworkResource rdfs:comment "Abstract grouping of Kubernetes kinds that govern network exposure and connectivity, such as Service, Ingress, and NetworkPolicy."@en .
kcro:ReplicaSet rdfs:comment "A workload kind that maintains a stable set of replica pods. Usually managed by a Deployment. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:Role rdfs:comment "A namespace-scoped RBAC role: a named set of permission rules applying within a single namespace. Modelled as a permission resource kind."@en .
kcro:Secret rdfs:comment "A Kubernetes object holding confidential data such as credentials or tokens, consumed by pods as environment variables or mounted files. Modelled as a data resource kind."@en .
kcro:Service rdfs:comment "A Kubernetes object that exposes a set of pods as a network service via a stable address and a label selector. Modelled as a network resource kind."@en .
kcro:ServiceAccount rdfs:comment "An identity that pods assume to authenticate to the Kubernetes API. Modelled as a permission resource kind."@en .
kcro:StatefulSet rdfs:comment "A workload kind that manages stateful pods with stable identities and persistent storage. Modelled as a workload-management resource kind."@en .
kcro:EnvReference rdfs:comment "A relator reifying a pod's consumption of a ConfigMap or Secret as environment variables; encodes containers[].envFrom[].configMapRef / .secretRef. Mediates the pod and the referenced data resource."@en .
kcro:IdentityAssignment rdfs:comment "A relator reifying the assignment of a ServiceAccount identity to a pod; encodes spec.serviceAccountName. Mediates the pod and the ServiceAccount."@en .
kcro:ImageReference rdfs:comment "A relator reifying a container's use of a container image; encodes containers[].image. Mediates the container and the ContainerImage."@en .
kcro:IngressBackend rdfs:comment "A relator reifying an Ingress rule routing to a backend Service; encodes spec.rules[].http.paths[].backend.service.name. Mediates the Ingress and the Service."@en .
kcro:NetworkPolicyScope rdfs:comment "A relator reifying the set of pods a NetworkPolicy applies to; encodes spec.podSelector.matchLabels resolved against pod labels. Mediates the NetworkPolicy and each selected pod."@en .
kcro:ServiceRouting rdfs:comment "A relator reifying a Service's selector-based routing to pods; encodes spec.selector resolved against pod labels (many-to-many, resolved at ingestion). Mediates the Service and each routed pod."@en .
kcro:VolumeMount rdfs:comment "A relator reifying a pod's mounting of a ConfigMap or Secret as a volume; encodes spec.volumes[].secret/.configMap. Mediates the pod and the referenced data resource."@en .
kcro:WorkloadManagement rdfs:comment "A relator reifying a controller's management of a pod template; encodes spec.template. Mediates the workload controller and the managed pod."@en .
kcro:ClusterIPExposure rdfs:comment "The exposure quality of a Service of type ClusterIP, reachable only within the cluster. A value-neutral fact, not a vulnerability."@en .
kcro:ExternalNameExposure rdfs:comment "The exposure quality of a Service of type ExternalName, which maps to an external DNS name. A value-neutral fact, not a vulnerability."@en .
kcro:LoadBalancerExposure rdfs:comment "The exposure quality of a Service of type LoadBalancer, provisioned with an external load balancer and reachable from outside the cluster. A value-neutral fact, not a vulnerability."@en .
kcro:NodePortExposure rdfs:comment "The exposure quality of a Service of type NodePort, reachable on a static port of every node and thus from outside the cluster. A value-neutral fact, not a vulnerability."@en .
kcro:ImageTagLatest rdfs:comment "The image-tag quality of a container whose image reference uses the mutable 'latest' tag, making the running version non-reproducible. A value-neutral quality with security relevance."@en .
kcro:ImageTagMissing rdfs:comment "The image-tag quality of a container whose image reference omits a tag (defaulting to 'latest'), making the running version non-reproducible. A value-neutral quality with security relevance."@en .
kcro:ThreatIntelDescriptor rdfs:comment "An information object that describes a KCRO entity in terms of an external threat-intelligence vocabulary (UCO, STIX, CWE), providing an attachment point for alignment without asserting class equivalence."@en .
kcro:causesLoss rdfs:comment "Relates a threat event to the loss event it brings about, following the COVER risk pattern."@en .
kcro:cweId rdfs:comment "Associates a KCRO vulnerability class with the identifier of the corresponding Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE) entry, where one applies."@en .
